# Recursion and execution-limit behavior regression cases (canonical)

# 1) Direct recursion should hit runtime execution guard (implementation policy)
# 実行時は ExecutionLimitExceeded 相当のエラーを期待
# A bare self-reference recurses; a vector literal does not (SPEC §4.3
# data-ization: `[ LOOP ]` is the data "LOOP", not a call).
# { LOOP } 'LOOP' DEF
# LOOP

# 2) Non-recursive custom word chain remains valid.
# Call STEP-A directly — a bare symbol inside `[ ... ]` is data, not a call.
{ [ 1 ] [ 2 ] + } 'STEP-A' DEF
{ STEP-A [ 3 ] + } 'STEP-B' DEF
STEP-B PRINT
# 期待: [ 6 ]

# 3) Recursive design is explicit opt-in and testable
# 下記は意図的にコメントアウトした失敗ケース（手動検証用）
# { NXT } 'NXT' DEF
# NXT
